The Chronicle Thandeka Moyo-Ndlovu, Health Reporter THE National Blood Services of Zimbabwe public affairs manager and spokesperson Ms Esther Massundah has died from Covid-19 related complications. The Zimbabwe Institute of Public Relations said Ms Massundah died on Tuesday morning and funeral arrangements will be announced in due course. “It is with a heavy heart that the Zimbabwe Institute of Public Relations notify you on the passing on of one of our members Esther Massundah who was leading the National Blood Services Communications strategy. Funeral arrangements will be announced in due course. Let’s remain resolute and steadfast in the fight against the covid-19 pandemic,” said the institute.